      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777060393429,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "He wants to use all of these pieces, with no piece left unused, to form a grid of dimensions n×m.\n\nGiven p and q, determine whether there exist positive integers n and m such that an n×m grid can be formed using exactly p unit-length \nsegments and q L-shaped pieces, possibly rotating them, and provide any valid n and m.",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "He wants to use all of these pieces, with no piece left unused, to form a grid of dimensions n×m.\n\nGiven p and q, determine whether there exist positive integers n and m such that an n×m grid can be formed using exactly p unit-length \nsegments and q L-shaped pieces, possibly rotating them, and provide any valid n and m.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
